1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,268
Lost instructions slow small businesses down. Binders, shared drives, group chats, and "ask someone who knows" all cost time.

2
00:00:08,268 --> 00:00:15,231
TechSavvy SOP Portal gives your team one branded home for the procedures they use every day.

3
00:00:15,231 --> 00:00:23,499
Staff can search by keyword, role, department, section, or daily workflow, then open the exact approved SOP they need.

4
00:00:23,499 --> 00:00:35,248
Every SOP can include a QR code, so employees can scan, open, and follow the right procedure on a phone or tablet, right where the work happens.

5
00:00:35,248 --> 00:00:44,822
Instead of hunting through documents, staff see the purpose, steps, attachments, validation notes, roles, and review status together on one clean screen.

6
00:00:44,822 --> 00:00:54,831
Managers can build the process library faster with AI-assisted SOP generation, then import existing procedure documents when you already have content to reuse.

7
00:00:54,831 --> 00:01:04,404
The editor keeps process details organized: owners, sections, roles, review dates, steps, validation, attachments, and approval workflow all stay in one place.

8
00:01:04,404 --> 00:01:13,107
When procedures change, version history and approvals help protect the current process, so staff are not relying on outdated instructions.

9
00:01:13,107 --> 00:01:21,811
Training tools turn written procedures into accountability. Add quiz questions, track training runs, and confirm that staff understand the work.

10
00:01:21,811 --> 00:01:31,819
Checklists turn repeatable work into daily action. Employees can complete task runs, add notes, and leave a clear record of what was done.

11
00:01:31,819 --> 00:01:41,393
When something is missing, outdated, or unclear, staff can suggest a change. Managers review, approve, and keep everyone using the current version.

12
00:01:41,393 --> 00:01:50,531
The manager dashboard gives leaders a quick view of SOP health, drafts, requests, user access, and the work that needs attention.

13
00:01:50,531 --> 00:01:59,670
Role-based access helps each person see what matters to their job, while managers keep control over users, logins, assignments, and permissions.

14
00:01:59,670 --> 00:02:10,114
Brand settings let every customer portal feel like their own, with company name, portal name, colors, logo, staff rules, mobile links, and QR settings.

15
00:02:10,114 --> 00:02:19,252
Built-in support requests give staff and managers a simple way to ask for help without losing the context of the portal.

16
00:02:19,252 --> 00:02:27,520
Backup, restore, export, and retention tools make the portal practical to support after launch, not just easy to demonstrate.

17
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:37,094
The result is less repeated training, fewer wrong steps, faster onboarding, and better protection for the knowledge that keeps your business running.

18
00:02:37,094 --> 00:02:48,408
TechSavvy SOP Portal is built for growing businesses with 5 to 250 users. Give your team one current answer, wherever the work happens. Book a demo.
